The paper discusses a method for improving the performance and stability of robotic applications using a combination of model-based and learning-based control methods. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of controllers to ensure stability and performance, which suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
